{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Diode Voltage Drop Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Diode Voltage Drop Demo",
    "description": "Plug in USB — both red LEDs light at once. The center branch is USB → 470Ω → LED → ground (brighter). The east branch adds a forward Schottky (90°, cathode toward the LED) before its LED, so roughly 0.3 V sits across the diode and less is left for the LED — it glows dimmer. Same resistor value; the difference is the diode drop, not resistance (compare lesson 5). LEDs at 90° (anode north)."
  },
